    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Bouncy Castles at Palexpo]]></title>
    <link href="http://playdegex.github.io/2011/11/bouncy-castles-at-palexpo/"/>
    <updated>2011-11-13T09:38:24+01:00</updated>
    <id>http://playdegex.github.io/2011/11/bouncy-castles-at-palexpo</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_o22J03lZ9Gw/TUW4mQpYSsI/AAAAAAAAzgk/CCVHBid2T0A/s1600/DSCN3085.JPG" imageanchor="1" style="clear: left; float: left; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="240" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_o22J03lZ9Gw/TUW4mQpYSsI/AAAAAAAAzgk/CCVHBid2T0A/s320/DSCN3085.JPG" width="320" /></a></div>


<p><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_o22J03lZ9Gw/TUW471LNHGI/AAAAAAAAzgo/l8A7ndvA8Gs/s1600/DSCN3077.JPG" imageanchor="1" style="clear: left; float: left; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="240" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_o22J03lZ9Gw/TUW471LNHGI/AAAAAAAAzgo/l8A7ndvA8Gs/s320/DSCN3077.JPG" width="320" /></a><br /><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_o22J03lZ9Gw/TUW5RzPQ54I/AAAAAAAAzgs/WQNQt81aznQ/s1600/DSCN3084.JPG" imageanchor="1" style="clear: left; float: left; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="240" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_o22J03lZ9Gw/TUW5RzPQ54I/AAAAAAAAzgs/WQNQt81aznQ/s320/DSCN3084.JPG" width="320" /></a><br /><a href="http://www.geneva-palexpo.ch/">Palexpo</a> is the Geneva exhibition centre near the airport normally reserved for the likes of the Geneva Motor Show. In the winter months, however, one of the halls is taken over by <a href="http://www.espacejunior.com/content/8-salles-de-jeux">Espace Junior</a>.<br /><br />The room is filled to bursting with bouncy castles, I counted at least 20 in total. There are also trampolines, battery go-karts and self propelled vehicles for the younger ones. This year the charge was 12 CHF for each child and adults were free, the go-karts require an extra token. There&rsquo;s a small shop selling ice-creams, coffee and beer. They have tables and benches to allow you to bring your own food or even host a children&rsquo;s birthday party. <br /><br />Certainly this place has to be visited at least once over the winter season.</p>
]]></content>
